// NucleoOS overview / meta cards — answer the "do you have a manual / how do I use the shell /
// what commands do you know" questions that pure per-command manual cards miss. Hand-written.
{"id": "os.manual", "category": "nucleoos", "action": "answer", "reply": {"it": "Si, ho il manuale di NucleoOS. Copre i comandi della shell (ls, cd, cat, grep, find, echo, mkdir, rm, cp, mv...) e delle guide (anima, desktop, status). Chiedimi 'come uso ls' o 'manuale di grep'.", "en": "Yes, I have the NucleoOS manual. It covers the shell commands (ls, cd, cat, grep, find, echo, mkdir, rm, cp, mv...) and guides (anima, desktop, status). Ask me 'how do i use ls' or 'grep manual'."}, "detail": {"it": "Ogni comando ha una pagina di manuale con sintassi, descrizione, opzioni, codici di ritorno ed esempi, in italiano e inglese. Le pagine vivono in /system/registry/manual ed sono usate sia dall'app Aiuto sia da me.", "en": "Each command has a manual page with synopsis, description, options, exit codes and examples, in Italian and English. The pages live in /system/registry/manual and are used by both the Help app and me."}, "ask": {"it": ["hai un manuale", "c'e un manuale", "esiste un manuale", "dov'e il manuale", "manuale", "guida", "aiuto sui comandi", "mostrami il manuale", "come trovo aiuto"], "en": ["do you have a manual", "is there a manual", "where is the manual", "manual", "user guide", "help with commands", "show me the manual", "how do i get help"]}, "source": "hand"}
{"id": "os.shell", "category": "nucleoos", "action": "answer", "reply": {"it": "NucleoOS ha una shell tipo POSIX: comandi come ls, cd, pwd, cat, grep, find, echo, mkdir, rm. Apri il Terminale e digita 'man <comando>' per la guida, oppure chiedi a me 'come uso <comando>'.", "en": "NucleoOS has a POSIX-like shell: commands such as ls, cd, pwd, cat, grep, find, echo, mkdir, rm. Open the Terminal and type 'man <command>' for help, or just ask me 'how do i use <command>'."}, "detail": {"it": "Il terminale invia le richieste al firmware via HTTP (es. ls chiama /api/fs/list). Supporta navigazione del filesystem sulla SD, lettura/scrittura file, e utility come grep e find. E' compatibile con un sottoinsieme POSIX.", "en": "The terminal sends requests to the firmware over HTTP (e.g. ls calls /api/fs/list). It supports SD filesystem navigation, file read/write, and utilities like grep and find. It is compatible with a POSIX subset."}, "ask": {"it": ["come uso la shell", "come funziona la shell", "cos'e la shell", "come uso il terminale", "come funziona il terminale", "cos'e il terminale di nucleoos", "come navigo nel filesystem"], "en": ["how do i use the shell", "how does the shell work", "what is the shell", "how do i use the terminal", "how does the terminal work", "what is the nucleoos terminal"]}, "source": "hand"}
{"id": "os.commands", "category": "nucleoos", "action": "answer", "reply": {"it": "I comandi shell che conosco: ls, cd, pwd, cat, grep, find, echo, mkdir, rm, cp, mv, touch, head, tail, wc, df, free, uname, uptime, date, ping, curl, wget, reboot, clear, history, theme. Chiedi 'come uso <comando>'.", "en": "The shell commands I know: ls, cd, pwd, cat, grep, find, echo, mkdir, rm, cp, mv, touch, head, tail, wc, df, free, uname, uptime, date, ping, curl, wget, reboot, clear, history, theme. Ask 'how do i use <command>'."}, "detail": {"it": "Ci sono comandi per il filesystem (ls, cd, cat, find, grep, cp, mv, rm, mkdir, touch), per lo stato del sistema (status, free, df, uname, uptime) e per la rete (ping, curl, wget). Ognuno ha una pagina di manuale completa.", "en": "There are filesystem commands (ls, cd, cat, find, grep, cp, mv, rm, mkdir, touch), system status commands (status, free, df, uname, uptime) and network commands (ping, curl, wget). Each has a full manual page."}, "ask": {"it": ["che comandi conosci", "quali comandi posso usare", "che comandi ci sono", "lista dei comandi", "elenco comandi", "che comandi della shell esistono", "cosa posso digitare nel terminale"], "en": ["what commands do you know", "which commands can i use", "list the commands", "what shell commands are there", "what can i type in the terminal"]}, "source": "hand"}
{"id": "os.intro", "category": "nucleoos", "action": "answer", "reply": {"it": "NucleoOS e un sistema operativo offline per il M5Stack Cardputer (ESP32-S3). Funziona senza internet, ha app, una shell con comandi e me, ANIMA, come assistente integrato.", "en": "NucleoOS is an offline operating system for the M5Stack Cardputer (ESP32-S3). It works without internet, has apps, a shell with commands, and me, ANIMA, as the built-in assistant."}, "detail": {"it": "Gira su un microcontrollore con poca memoria, quindi e progettato per essere leggero: allocazione statica, dati sulla SD, nessun modello generativo. L'interfaccia e una PWA accessibile da browser oltre che dallo schermo del device.", "en": "It runs on a low-memory microcontroller, so it is designed to be lightweight: static allocation, data on the SD card, no generative model. The interface is a PWA reachable from a browser as well as the device screen."}, "ask": {"it": ["cos'e nucleoos", "cos'e nucleo os", "cos'e nucleo", "cos'e nucleos", "che cos'e nucleoos", "cosa e nucleoos", "cosa sai di nucleoos", "parlami di nucleoos", "come funziona nucleoos", "come funziona nucleo"], "en": ["what is nucleoos", "what is nucleo os", "what is nucleo", "tell me about nucleoos", "how does nucleoos work"]}, "source": "hand"}
